The Ukrainian state news agency reported that Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan invited Russian President Vladimir Putin and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky to meet in Turkey to discuss differences and overcome problems. According to the report, Turkish presidential spokesperson Ibrahim Kalin said Erdogan would visit Ukraine in a few weeks and meet with Zelensky. (Cover: File photo of Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan, December 16, 2021. /CFP)